		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2009"></a><br><code>sle2009/paper23</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2009</a> paper:</span><br><i>Closing the Gap between Modelling and Java</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/FlorianHeidenreich.html">Florian Heidenreich</a>, <a href="../profile/JendrikJohannes.html">Jendrik Johannes</a>, <a href="../profile/MirkoSeifert.html">Mirko Seifert</a>, <a href="../profile/ChristianWende.html">Christian Wende</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_25">10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_25</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagM">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It provides bidirectional conversion between Java text and model representations (parser/printer), i.e., mapping/conversion.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagL">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> It defines a full Java metamodel and related specifications, which is a meta-language/metamodeling contribution.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1b.html"><span class="tagL">T1B: Static Semantics</span></a><ul><li> It reflects Java’s static semantics via cross-references and resolution, emphasizing static-semantics handling.
</li></ul></li></ul>
